{
  "texts": [
    "(d) Implementation Bug: It might be possible that even the generated assertions are correct, but the implementation might be buggy.",
    "In such a scenario, the testcase fails, giving wrong outputs.",
    "In this case, manual inspection of design implementation is to be done as shown in Line 23 of Algorithm 1.The assertions may not pass the testcases in a single run.",
    "Therefore, we iteratively run the error-checking process multiple times.",
    "Line 11 of Algorithm 1 shows that the while loop runs until n is less than the upper bound T. If n gets equal to T, and there are still error messages in W log, we manually investigate and resolve the potential issue which LLM cannot fix automatically and restart the assertion generation process as stated in Lines 29-33.The proposed ChIRAAG framework is illustrated in the Fig. 1."
  ]
}